ke the competition effective. </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">hose are important issues. It is not, I do not think, the planning round that will reveal those</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> I think </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">they</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> have to be dealt with in parallel with the planning round.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Dr Wollaston:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> But </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">would</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal"> you be looking—</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Chair:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Sarah, that is a taster, if I may say so, of the discussion </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">about</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> competition which is to come after this Division and after David </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Tredinnick</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> has had his question when we get back. We will come back as quick</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> as we can.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Sitting suspended for a Division in the House.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-indent:36pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">On resuming—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Chair:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">If we may, let us get started. I understand it is unlikely</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">but not certainly so</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">that we shall be disturbed again by a vote. Let us hope not. David </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Tredinnick</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> has a question to ask you specifically on the funding gap and all that</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> but so does Andrew George</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">. S</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">o can we go to him first, then back to David and then </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">to Sarah on competition?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q10 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Andrew George:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> In terms of “C</span><span sty