</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Morecambe</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Bay</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> less likely are the changes going on with the CQC</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> Morecambe Bay I think illustrates this. When we were assessing </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Morecambe</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Bay</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> for FT status we spotted that there was a pattern of worrying SUIs</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">serious untoward incidents</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">in particular in maternity</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">. S</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">o we stopped our assessment and said to the CQC, </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Can you go and have a look because we are not sure there is not a problem here,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">eventually they came back and said, </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">No, it is fine.</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garam